parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or surge unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the throttle body light comes on
the vehicle surges or lurches forward
the engine idles poorly
the vehicle hesitates while driving at lower speeds
the accelerator pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle loses power
and the ETS light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control and ABS systems can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or surge unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the ABS and brake lights illuminate

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the engine to stall, hesitate, or surge, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling
hesitation
or surging
especially when accelerating or decelerating; check engine light illumination; difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch or transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or lose power, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor

hesitation or loss of power when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and hesitation can cause loss of control and potential accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.

hesitation
or surging

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or hesitate to accelerate, leading to unsafe operating conditions and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
hesitates to accelerate
surges or idles roughly
and the "ETS" or "Check Engine" lights come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and brake system can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the defroster can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The windows frost up or fog excessively
